            "name": "Depth Charge",
            "saving_throw": [
              {
                "basic": true,
                "dc": 22,
                "save_type": "Fort",
                "subtype": "save_dc",
                "text": "DC 22 basic Fortitude save",
                "type": "stat_block_section"
              }
            ],
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The marauder pulls a release valve on their suit, expelling a pressure wave that deals 3d6 sonic and 3d6 bludgeoning damage (DC 22 basic Fortitude save) to all creatures in a 10-foot emanation. Creatures that fail the save take a \u20132 circumstance penalty to Acrobatics checks to Balance and Athletics checks to Swim for 1 minute as their inner ear is impaired. Creatures that critically fail the save are also deafened for 1 minute. The marauder can't use Depth Charge again for 1d4 rounds.",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 5,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "8ca8a0ac0e16b3c136f09ca48d8578bb",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Air",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 452,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Effects with the air trait either manipulate or conjure air. Those that manipulate air have no effect in a vacuum or an area without air. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of air or have a connection to magical air.   \n  \nPlanes with this trait consist mostly of open spaces and air of various levels of turbulence, though they also contain rare islands of floating stone and other elements and energies. Air planes usually have breathable atmospheres, though they might include clouds of acidic or toxic gas. Earth creatures often find themselves at a disadvantage within air planes, as there\u2019s little solid ground for them to gain their bearings, which tends to at least make them uncomfortable.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 104,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "6a0bf3cdfe7c0fc427c7b8ea9310f113",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Manipulate",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 458,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "You must physically manipulate an item or make gestures to use an action with this trait. Creatures without a suitable appendage can\u2019t perform actions with this trait. Manipulate actions often trigger reactions.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 147,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "062d349c50c70477d316b8620025454e",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Sonic",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 461",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 461",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 461,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An effect with the sonic trait functions only if it makes sound, meaning it has no effect in an area of silence or in a vacuum. This is different from an auditory spell, which is effective only if the target can hear it. A sonic effect might deal sonic damage.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
